|year=1960
|author={{w|P. G. Wodehouse}}
|title={{w|Jeeves in the Offing}}
|section=chapter VIII
|passage=“You did come down a wallop, didn't you? How art thou fallen from heaven, oh Lucifer, son of the morning, I said to myself. You're so terribly '''neurotic''', Bertie. You must try to be less jumpy. What you need is a good nerve tonic.”}}
